The paper proposes a kernel learning framework for improving the generalization performance of kernel methods. This is a topic that is commonly studied in the machine learning community, particularly in the subfield of statistical learning theory (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of non-stationary spectral kernels, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of regularization terms to improve performance, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and optimization (cs.SD). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SD.
